  "texts": [
    "Parallelly, there were efforts to optimize the computational efficiency of these models, focusing on reducing the substantial energy and resource requirements [17,18].",
    "Innovations in model architectures led to more advanced understanding of natural language, allowing for better handling of subtleties like sarcasm and indirect speech [19,20].",
    "Efforts were also made to integrate multimodal inputs, enabling LLMs to process and respond to a combination of text, image, and voice data [21][22][23].",
    "Another significant development was the customization of LLMs for specific industries, such as legal or medical, tailoring their outputs to suit domain-specific needs [24,25].",
    "Lastly, the integration of real-time data streams opened new avenues for LLMs, allowing them to provide responses that were not only contextually relevant but also current and timely [7,26]."
